From: Tariq Toukan <tariqt@nvidia.com>
Date: Wed, 30 Dec 2020 11:53:14 +0200
Subject: net/mlx5: Node-aware allocation for the EQ table
Patch-mainline: v5.18-rc1
Git-commit: e894246df5136f670f3568b7856daeec6c4f9456
References: jsc#PED-1549

Prefer the aware allocation, use the device NUMA node.

Signed-off-by: Tariq Toukan <tariqt@nvidia.com>
Reviewed-by: Moshe Shemesh <moshe@nvidia.com>
Signed-off-by: Saeed Mahameed <saeedm@nvidia.com>
Acked-by: Thomas Bogendoerfer <tbogendoerfer@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlx5/core/eq.c |    3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlx5/core/eq.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/mellanox/mlx5/core/eq.c
@@ -438,7 +438,8 @@ int mlx5_eq_table_init(struct mlx5_core_
 	struct mlx5_eq_table *eq_table;
 	int i;
 
-	eq_table = kvzalloc(sizeof(*eq_table), GFP_KERNEL);
+	eq_table = kvzalloc_node(sizeof(*eq_table), GFP_KERNEL,
+				 dev->priv.numa_node);
 	if (!eq_table)
 		return -ENOMEM;
 
